{"word":"φρεαττώ","slug":"φρεαττώ","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<entryFree id=\"n112263\" key=\"freattw/\" type=\"main\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"entryFree\"> <orth extent=\"full\" lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"orth\">φρεαττώ</orth> or <orth extent=\"full\" lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"orth\">φρεᾱτώ</orth>, <itype lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"itype\">οῦς</itype>, <gen lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"gen\">ἡ</gen>, a court in Peiraeus, where banished men accused of murder were allowed to present themselves for trial, the accused being on board ship, the judges on shore; only dat. (loc.), <sense id=\"n112263.0\" n=\"A\" level=\"1\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"sense\"> <cit TEIform=\"cit\"> <quote_ lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"quote\">ἐν Φρεαττοῖ</quote_> <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0014.tlg023.perseus-grc1:77\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ D.\">D.</a></author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">23.77</biblScope></bibl></cit>,<bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">78</biblScope></bibl>, <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0086.tlg035.perseus-grc1:1300b:29\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Arist.\">Arist.</a></author> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Pol.\">Pol.</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">1300b29</biblScope> </bibl>:—the nom. is written <orth extent=\"full\" lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"orth\">φρεαττύς</orth> in <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0525.tlg001.perseus-grc1:1:28:11\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\">Paus.</author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">1.28.11</biblScope></bibl>.</sense> </entryFree>"}]}